Augmented.Object.html.title: Object
Augmented.Object.html.name: Object
Augmented.Object.html.description: Augmented ObjectBase class for other classes to extend from

Augmented.Object.html#.listenTo.title: <static> listenTo( obj, name, callback )
Augmented.Object.html#.listenTo.name: listenTo
Augmented.Object.html#.listenTo.description: Inversion-of-control versions of on. Tell this object to listen toan event in another object... keeping track of what it's listening tofor easier unbinding later.

Augmented.Object.html#.on.title: <static> on( name, callback, context )
Augmented.Object.html#.on.name: on
Augmented.Object.html#.on.description: Bind an event to a callback function. Passing "all" will bindthe callback to all events fired.

Augmented.Object.html#.off.title: <static> off( name, callback, context )
Augmented.Object.html#.off.name: off
Augmented.Object.html#.off.description: Remove one or many callbacks. If context is null, removes allcallbacks with that function. If callback is null, removes allcallbacks for the event. If name is null, removes all boundcallbacks for all events.

Augmented.Object.html#.once.title: <static> once( name, callback, context )
Augmented.Object.html#.once.name: once
Augmented.Object.html#.once.description: Bind an event to only be triggered a single time. After the first timethe callback is invoked, its listener will be removed. If multiple eventsare passed in using the space-separated syntax, the handler will fireonce for each event, not once for a combination of all events.

Augmented.Object.html#.trigger.title: <static> trigger( name, args )
Augmented.Object.html#.trigger.name: trigger
Augmented.Object.html#.trigger.description: Trigger one or many events, firing all bound callbacks. Callbacks arepassed the same arguments as trigger is, apart from the event name(unless you're listening on "all", which will cause your callback toreceive the true name of the event as the first argument).

Augmented.Object.html#.stopListening.title: <static> stopListening( obj, name, callback )
Augmented.Object.html#.stopListening.name: stopListening
Augmented.Object.html#.stopListening.description: Tell this object to stop listening to either specific events ... orto every object it's currently listening to.

Augmented.Utility.MessageReader.html#.ge.title: <static> getMessage( key )
Augmented.Utility.MessageReader.html#.ge.name: getMessage
Augmented.Utility.MessageReader.html#.ge.description: getMessage - get the message out of the bundle.If message is not found, then ResourceBundle returns the keywrapped in square bracketsloop through the fallback path of the key by removing thelast attribute and searching the bundle againstop when you get back a real message (not just the [key])

Augmented.Utility.MessageKeyFormatter.ht.title: MessageKeyFormatter
Augmented.Utility.MessageKeyFormatter.ht.name: MessageKeyFormatter
Augmented.Utility.MessageKeyFormatter.ht.description: Augmented.Utility.MessageKeyFormatterConcatenate the pieces of the message together if a portion of the key ismissing, the rest of the key is ignored. ex. if the "rule" attribute ismissing, then the key will return with the message.level + message.kind only
